# Project: next-template

Next.js 16 App Router + MUI 7 + Zustand 5 + next-intl 4 + TypeScript 5 + React 19.

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — development server
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm run lint` — ESLint check
- `npm run lint-fix` — ESLint auto-fix

## Architecture

- All routes under `src/app/[locale]/` (locale-prefixed: en, hy, ru)
- Server components by default — `"use client"` only for hooks, event handlers, browser APIs
- Zustand slices hold state only — mutations via `setAppStore()`, reads via external selectors
- MUI theme with CSS variables, light/dark via `data-color-scheme`
- Emotion CSS-in-JS for styling
- Translations: `useTranslator()` client-side, `getTranslations()` server-side
- Path alias: `@/*` resolves to `./src/*`

## Component Structure

Each component in own directory:
- `Component.tsx` — UI only, props interface, no business logic
- `styled.tsx` — styled MUI components (`"use client"` required)
- `index.ts` — named re-export

## Code Rules

- Function expressions only (`const fn = () => {}`), never `function fn() {}`
  - Exception: `export default function` for Next.js pages/layouts
- Functions with 2+ params use single object argument
- Import order: Framework > Third-party > Local (blank lines between groups)
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- PascalCase components, camelCase hooks, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE constants
- `I` prefix for store interfaces (e.g., `IAppStore`)
- Max 250 lines per file, max nesting depth 3, max complexity 10
- No `console.log` — only `console.warn` and `console.error`
